<P>Vindiciae Literarum, THE SCHOOLS GVARDED: OR, The excellency and usefulnesse of Arts, Sciences, Languages, History, and all sorts of humane Learning, in subordinati|on to Divinity, &amp; Preparation for the Mynistry, by ten Arguments evinced, ten cavils rai|sed against it by Familists, Anabap|tists, Antinomians, Lutherans, Li|bertines, &amp;c. are refelled and answered, and many cau|tions to prevent all mistakes are added.</P>
<P>By THOMAS HALL, <HI>B. D.</HI> and Pastour of <HI>KINGS-NORTON.</HI></P>
<Q><BIBL><HI>Iohn 5.39.</HI> </BIBL>
<P>Search the Scriptures.</P></Q>
<Q><P>Quaerite legendo, &amp; invenietis meditando, pulsate orando, &amp; aperietur vobis contemplando.</P>
